{"type":"message","id":"e8a8ec2c","parentId":"ced9fc87","timestamp":"2026-03-04T23:33:47.600Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"   Now I have a good picture. Let me understand what needs to be done:\n\n1. **anchor-v2.sh** - Already exists but is incomplete (it's a stub/minimal version that doesn't do much). The current anchor.sh is the full version with semantic support. The v2 seems to be an incomplete version. Based on the current v2, I need to:\n   - Make it actually functional like anchor.sh\n   - Add proper QMD semantic search integration\n   - Add support for detecting current task, decisions, open loops\n   - The current v2 is very minimal\n\n2. **context-recover.sh** - Doesn't exist. Based on SKILL.md, this should be an alias/wrapper or a separate script that likely calls anchor.sh with --semantic mode\n\n3. **qmd embed** - Already ran and completed! 4 documents embedded.\n\n4. **AGENTS.md** - Needs updating with the new startup protocol (adding anchor.sh to the \"Every Session\" routine)\n\nLet me formulate the analysis and plan:\n\n**Analysis:**\n- anchor-v2.sh exists but is incomplete (basic stub)\n- context-recover.sh doesn't exist\n- QMD embed completed (4 docs, 5 chunks embedded)\n- AGENTS.md needs updating with the anchor script in the \"Every Session\" protocol\n\n**Plan:**\n1. Rewrite anchor-v2.sh with proper QMD integration (similar to anchor.sh but cleaner/better)\n2. Create context-recover.sh as a symlink or wrapper calling anchor.sh --semantic\n3. Verify qmd embedding (already done!)\n4. Update AGENTS.md \"Every Session\" section to add the anchor script\n\nLet me proceed with","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"text","text":" Now I have a complete picture. Let me analyze and plan:\n\n## Analysis\n\n| Task | Current State | Gap |\n|------|--------------|-----|\n| **1. anchor-v2.sh** | Exists as stub with minimal QMD integration | Needs full implementation like anchor.sh but cleaner |\n| **2. context-recover.sh** | Doesn't exist | Create as wrapper/alias calling anchor with --semantic |\n| **3. qmd embed** | ✅ Completed! (4 docs, 5 chunks in 11s) | Verified |\n| **4. AGENTS.md** | Has old \"Every Session\" protocol | Add anchor.sh to startup routine |\n\n---\n\n## PLAN — Validation Checkpoint\n\n### Phase 1: anchor-v2.sh (Proper QMD Integration)\n- Rewrite with full feature parity to anchor.sh\n- Cleaner arg parsing, better QMD semantic search\n- Add `--save` flag to write context snaps to `context/active/`\n- Add filtering modes (--decided, --pending, --blocked)\n\n### Phase 2: context-recover.sh  \n- Create semantic-focused wrapper\n- Defaults to `--semantic` mode\n- Auto-saves snapshot for persistence\n\n### Phase 3: Verify QMD Embed\n- Already completed: 4 docs, 5 chunks embedded\n\n### Phase 4: AGENTS.md Update\n- Add anchor.sh call to \"Every Session\" routine (position 1)\n- Reference QMD integration\n\n---\n\n**Does this plan align with your intent? Confirm and I'll proceed with implementation.** 🦞\n\n(Detected: Today is 2026-03-05. Last daily file: 03/03.md. Will scan both QMD and flat structures where available.)"}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"nvidia","model":"moonshotai/kimi-k2.5","usage":{"input":26186,"output":695,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":26881,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1772667179138}}
